# Teammate Sync Rule

This rule ensures all Teammate framework improvements discovered during project work flow back to the central Teammate repository.

## Central Repository

**Teammate Hub**: `[TEAMMATE_HUB_PATH]`

> 安裝時請將 `[TEAMMATE_HUB_PATH]` 替換為實際的 Teammate 專案路徑（例如 `D:\Teammate` 或 `/Users/me/Developer/Teammate`）。

This is the single source of truth for the Teammate framework. All projects share this same hub.

## Sync: Framework Files

Whenever the user requests changes to any of the following files in this project:

- `.cursor/rules/teammate-rules.mdc`
- `.cursor/commands/teammate.*.md`
- `.cursor/commands/teammate.helpme.md`

The AI MUST also apply the same changes to the corresponding files in the Teammate Hub:

- `[TEAMMATE_HUB_PATH]/.cursor/rules/teammate-rules.mdc`
- `[TEAMMATE_HUB_PATH]/.cursor/commands/teammate.*.md`
- `[TEAMMATE_HUB_PATH]/.cursor/commands/helpme.md`

## Sync: Version Tracking

When framework files are changed in the Hub, the AI SHOULD remind the user to:

1. Update `[TEAMMATE_HUB_PATH]/CHANGELOG.md` — add changes to `[Unreleased]` section
2. Bump `[TEAMMATE_HUB_PATH]/.teammate/config/teammate.yml` version when releasing
3. Run `/teammate.helpme migrate` in other projects to apply the changes

## Sync: Lessons Learned

Whenever the AI discovers a workflow improvement, rule addition, or process insight during project work, it MUST append the learning to:

- `[TEAMMATE_HUB_PATH]/PLAYBOOK.md` → Section 1「歷史修改軌跡」

Format（結構化欄位，每筆一個 block）:
```
#### YYYY-MM-DD · 類型 · 專案
**觸發**: [what went wrong or could be better]
**決策**: [what was changed]
**影響**: [affected files/commands]
**成效**: [observed improvement, or 待驗證]
**狀態**: 生效中
```

類型可選：規則 / 命令 / 架構 / 模板 / 腳本 / 文件 / 技能 / 測試

This ensures all projects contribute to a centralized memory that any future AI session can learn from.

## Rules

- **Always sync to Hub**: Changes to framework files must propagate to the Teammate Hub
- **Announce the sync**: After updating, explicitly confirm which files were synced
- **Do not ask for permission to sync**: The sync is automatic as long as this rule is active
- **Preserve project-specific content**: Only sync Teammate framework files, not project-specific rules or features
- **PLAYBOOK is append-only**: Never remove existing entries from the history track (Section 1)

## What to Sync vs What NOT to Sync

| Sync to Teammate Hub | Do NOT sync (project-specific) |
|----------------------|-------------------------------|
| `teammate-rules.mdc` | `backtest_rules.mdc` or other project rules |
| `teammate.*.md` commands (incl. helpme) | `.teammate/memory/` contents |
| Lessons to `PLAYBOOK.md` | `tasks/` artifacts |
| Changes to `CHANGELOG.md` | `.cursorule` (User Profile) |
| | `docs/` (project-specific docs) |